OL,3,CWhat is behind the 'eerie' spring
OL,4,Cphenomenon covering Britain's
OL,5,Chedgerows?
OL,7,FOn warm evenings in late spring,
OL,8,Fhedgerows across parts of Britain
OL,9,Fappear to glow white in the fading
OL,10,Flight.
OL,12,FIt begins as a shimmer but turns to
OL,13,Fscenes I'd liken to Hammer House of
OL,14,FHorror.
OL,16,FFor the unknowing, the sight is eerie
OL,17,Fand alarming, with social media
OL,18,Ffilling with speculation about
OL,19,Finvasive spider species, toxic mould
OL,20,For even environmental catastrophe.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/10
