FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1778746039
OL,3,CWhat is behind the 'eerie' spring
OL,4,Cphenomenon covering Britain's
OL,5,Chedgerows?
OL,7,FThese dense silk tents create a mini
OL,8,Fsheltered ecosystem for the
OL,9,Fcaterpillars; warmer, rainproof, and
OL,10,Freduced exposure to predators.
OL,12,FHawthorn, blackthorn, spindle, and
OL,13,Fbird cherry bushes seem to be
OL,14,Fparticularly at risk from infestation,
OL,15,Fbut occasionally whole trees can be
OL,16,Fshrouded in the dense white webbing.
OL,18,FThe phenomenon has become increasingly
OL,19,Fvisible in recent years, partly
OL,20,Fbecause mild springs can help
OL,21,Fcaterpillar survival rates.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
