PN,31805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1778746039
OL,3,CWhat is behind the 'eerie' spring
OL,4,Cphenomenon covering Britain's
OL,5,Chedgerows?
OL,7,FAre they harmful?
OL,9,FWhile they may look alarming - even
OL,10,Fgaining the nickname "ghost hedges" in
OL,11,Fsome areas - they are not at all
OL,12,Fdangerous.
OL,14,FThey do not sting, bite, or carry
OL,15,Fvenom, and the silk covering the
OL,16,Fhedges is harmless.
OL,18,FUnlike some caterpillars, they do not
OL,19,Fhave toxic hairs that can irritate
OL,20,Fskin or cause breathing problems.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
