PN,31806
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1778746039
OL,3,CWhat is behind the 'eerie' spring
OL,4,Cphenomenon covering Britain's
OL,5,Chedgerows?
OL,7,FDogs and cats are generally fine
OL,8,Faround them, too, although pets should
OL,9,Fstill be discouraged from eating large
OL,10,Fnumbers of any caterpillars because it
OL,11,Fcould upset their stomachs. Also, it's
OL,12,Fpretty gross!
OL,14,FThe main impact is on the plants.
OL,16,FThe caterpillars have voracious
OL,17,Fappetites and often strip a hedge or
OL,18,Ftree back to its bare branches to the
OL,19,Fextent that it appears to have died.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
