PN,31809
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1778746039
OL,3,CWhat is behind the 'eerie' spring
OL,4,Cphenomenon covering Britain's
OL,5,Chedgerows?
OL,7,FWe've also seen wider shifts in insect
OL,8,Fbehaviour in recent years, with
OL,9,Fspecies emerging earlier in the
OL,10,Fcalendar due to rising temperatures.
OL,12,FFor now, though, the "ghost hedges"
OL,13,Fremain more curiosity than crisis.
